# Bash Script Execution on Windows

For executing bash scripts (*.sh files) on Windows systems through PowerShell, use this command format:

```powershell
& "C:\Program Files\Git\bin\bash.exe" -c "./script-name.sh [arguments]"
```

## Example:
- `& "C:\Program Files\Git\bin\bash.exe" -c "./vps-manager.sh bot-logs"`
